<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idee6118e9-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s940h"><num value="940h">§ 940h.</num><heading> Bonding requirements</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall review the bonding requirements for all programs administered by the Rural Utilities Service under this chapter to ensure that bonds are not required if—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idee6118ea-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s940h/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the interests of the Secretary are adequately protected by product warranties; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idee6118eb-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s940h/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the costs or conditions associated with a bond exceed the benefit of the bond.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idee6118ec-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1936-05-20/ch432">May 20, 1936, ch. 432</ref>, title III, § 318, as added <ref href="/us/pl/110/234/tVI/s6109">Pub. L. 110–234, title VI, § 6109</ref>, <date date="2008-05-22">May 22, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/1198">122 Stat. 1198</ref>, and <ref href="/us/pl/110/246/s4/a">Pub. L. 110–246, § 4(a)</ref>, title VI, § 6109, <date date="2008-06-18">June 18, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/1664">122 Stat. 1664</ref>, 1960.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idee6118ed-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idee6118ee-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idee6118ef-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><ref href="/us/pl/110/234">Pub. L. 110–234</ref> and <ref href="/us/pl/110/246">Pub. L. 110–246</ref> enacted identical sections. <ref href="/us/pl/110/234">Pub. L. 110–234</ref> was repealed by <ref href="/us/pl/110/246/s4/a">section 4(a) of Pub. L. 110–246</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idee6118f0-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idee6118f1-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Enactment of this section and repeal of <ref href="/us/pl/110/234">Pub. L. 110–234</ref> by <ref href="/us/pl/110/246">Pub. L. 110–246</ref> effective <date date="2008-05-22">May 22, 2008</date>, the date of enactment of <ref href="/us/pl/110/234">Pub. L. 110–234</ref>, see <ref href="/us/pl/110/246/s4">section 4 of Pub. L. 110–246</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s8701">section 8701 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
